Tell me about the treaty on strategic offensive reductions The treaty on strategic offensive reductions, also known as the New START treaty, is a bilateral treaty between the United States and the Russian Federation that entered into force on February 5, 2011. The treaty limits the number of nuclear warheads that each country can have to 1,550. It also requires that both countries provide regular updates on their nuclear arsenals.

define silicon tell me more about silicon Silicon is a chemical element with symbol Si and atomic number 14. It is a hard and brittle crystalline solid with a blue-gray metallic luster. It is a tetravalent metalloid. Silicon is the eighth most common element in the universe by mass, but very rarely occurs as the pure element in nature. It is most widely distributed in dusts, sands, and planets as various forms of silicon dioxide (silica) or silicates

what happened to computers in the year 2000 tell me more about the year 2000 The year 2000 was a significant year for computers because it was when the Y2K problem was supposed to occur. Fortunately, the problem was largely resolved and there were no major disruptions caused by the change in date.

This could cause systems to believe it is the year 1900 instead of 2000, and may cause errors in calculations, programs, and data.
